		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Personally, I haven't noticed much of an improvement going from RF to composite video on the NES, but I don't have the equipment to make the comparison at the moment.  The only reason to use RF is that it is likely to involve less drastic alterations to the top-loader's PCB.  (No need to cut the video line to the RF unit or solder directly to the PPU pin.)

		

