	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The PPU generates colors by oscillating between high and low voltages. The best possible way to generate S-video without swapping out the PPU would involve tracking the master and pixel clocks somehow, determining the high and low voltages for a given pixel, sending the average on the luma pair, and sending the difference on the chroma pair.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


