		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">TheDruidXpawX wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Greetings. I've been looking through this thread, trying to determine if there's any hope for the video on my top loader NES. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />If I get my facts straight...<br />1) It seems that the well documented A/V Mod isn't sufficient to clean up the video.<br />2) You can use some component from a toaster style NES to fix the video, and also have A/V out, but it wont fit in the top loader box.<br /><br /></div>
<br />
<br />It appears the reason for the 'lines' on the toploader's video is the PPU.  It is a revision H PPU, which is only found in the toploaders.  The front loaders all use revision G PPUs.  
<br />
<br />So, you could try swapping out the PPU from a front loader to see if it fixes the problem.  I suspect it will.
<br />
<br />I want to do this mod to my toploader, but I just have never gotten around to doing it.

		

